input.content:
Implemented stream-mode `reverse` for Camel's Resequencer EIP. Key design: reversal must NOT be a simple negated compare() — ResequencerEngine uses predecessor()/successor() to decide when to cancel scheduled timeouts vs deliver, so a wrapper comparator must negate compare() AND swap predecessor<->successor.

New file: core/camel-core-processor/src/main/java/org/apache/camel/processor/resequencer/ReverseSequenceElementComparator.java
```java
public class ReverseSequenceElementComparator<E> implements SequenceElementComparator<E> {
    private final SequenceElementComparator<E> delegate;
    public int compare(E o1, E o2) { return delegate.compare(o2, o1); }
    public boolean predecessor(E o1, E o2) { return delegate.successor(o1, o2); }
    public boolean successor(E o1, E o2) { return delegate.predecessor(o1, o2); }
    public boolean isValid(E o1) { return delegate.isValid(o1); }
}
```

Wiring (mirrors existing batch `reverse` pattern in BatchResequencerConfig/Resequencer):
- StreamResequencerConfig.java: added `reverse` String field (@XmlAttribute, @Metadata(label="advanced", javaType="java.lang.Boolean")), getter/setter, added to copy ctor.
- ResequenceDefinition.reverse(): previously threw IllegalStateException when streamConfig != null; now branches - sets streamConfig.setReverse(true) for stream, else existing batch behavior.
- StreamResequencer.java: added 5-arg ctor (camelContext, processor, comparator, expression, reverse) that wraps comparator in ReverseSequenceElementComparator when reverse=true before building ResequencerEngine; old 4-arg ctor delegates with reverse=false. Added `isReverse()` getter (no setter - engine/comparator immutable post-construction).
- ResequenceReifier.createStreamResequencer(): parses `isReverse = parseBoolean(config.getReverse(), false)`, passes to new 5-arg StreamResequencer ctor.
- ManagedResequencer.isReverse() (JMX): now returns getStreamResequencer().isReverse() in the else branch instead of null.
- Generated JSON metadata updated in two places to add index-6 `reverse` property mirroring batchConfig.json's format: core/camel-core-model/src/generated/resources/META-INF/org/apache/camel/model/config/streamConfig.json and catalog/camel-catalog/src/generated/resources/org/apache/camel/catalog/models/streamConfig.json.

Verified by design (not scoped out): rejectOld composes correctly with reverse automatically because beforeLastDelivered() in ResequencerEngine uses the same compare() that gets correctly negated by the wrapper - no special-casing needed.

Acceptance test (must not be modified): core/camel-core/src/test/java/org/apache/camel/processor/StreamResequencerReverseGateTest.java - route `.resequence(header("seqnum")).stream().reverse().timeout(750)`.

